
                        Section 2 - Notes
                         ARG Instruction

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    FROM ubuntu
    ARG username="10"
    ARG appdir
    COPY text? /$appdir/
    WORKDIR $appdir/
    USER $username
    CMD ["/bin/bash"]

2.  Build without ARGs set for username and appdir.

    $ docker build -t arg . 

    $ docker run -it arg
    uucp@d1321e494249:/$ ls
    bin   dev  home  lib64  mnt  proc  run  srv  text1  text3  usr
    boot  etc  lib   media  opt  root  sbin sys  text2  tmp    var
    uucp@d1321e494249:/$ exit

    Shell prompt shows USER is uucp (10) and 
    appdir is / since no ARGS were set.

3.  Build with appdir set.

    $ docker build -t arg --build-arg appdir="tmp" . 

    $ docker run -it arg
    uucp@6bb900af1cea:/tmp$ ls
    text1  text2  text3
    uucp@6bb900af1cea:/tmp$ exit

    Shell prompt shows USER is uucp (10) and appdir is /tmp.

4.  Build with appdir and username set.

    $ docker build -t arg --build-arg appdir="tmp" \
           --build-arg username="5" . 

    $ docker run -it arg
    games@161c451a5d48:/tmp$ ls
    text1  text2  text3
    games@161c451a5d48:/tmp$ exit

    Shell prompt shows USER is games (5) and appdir is /tmp.

